00:52:28.000 --> 00:52:29.150
we'll link to it, yeah.

00:52:30.300 --> 00:52:34.410
- What we do is describe,
the first two chapters

00:52:34.410 --> 00:52:38.340
present to the layperson
a clear simple explanation

00:52:38.340 --> 00:52:43.340
of global warming and why the
science is utterly believable

00:52:43.840 --> 00:52:46.140
and why we should be concerned

00:52:46.140 --> 00:52:47.810
and why we need to take action.

00:52:47.810 --> 00:52:51.440
The next nine chapters
talk about what to do

00:52:51.440 --> 00:52:55.030
and we present a complete coherent plan,

00:52:55.030 --> 00:52:57.770
the technology, the
economics, and the policy

00:52:57.770 --> 00:52:59.910
for achieving a solution.

00:52:59.910 --> 00:53:02.870
And we do this, by the way,

00:53:02.870 --> 00:53:04.610
without any carbon sequestration

00:53:05.945 --> 00:53:09.573
because I not persuaded
that it's plausible

00:53:10.450 --> 00:53:12.650
to sequester carbon and we do it

00:53:12.650 --> 00:53:16.630
without a large commitment to biofuels

00:53:16.630 --> 00:53:20.160
because I'm very concerned
about the competition

00:53:20.160 --> 00:53:22.830
for land between food,
which we're going to need

00:53:22.830 --> 00:53:25.820
more and more of in the
future as population grows

00:53:25.820 --> 00:53:29.010
and land for biofuels, so no biofuels,

00:53:29.010 --> 00:53:34.010
no carbon sequestration,
nuclear we don't require it,

00:53:35.560 --> 00:53:39.290
it's there, but we're not
asking for an expansion of it.

00:53:39.290 --> 00:53:43.230
We rely on efficiency, wind, solar,

00:53:43.230 --> 00:53:46.750
and some geothermal, a lot of efficiency.

00:53:46.750 --> 00:53:48.530
You had an interview with Amory Lovins

00:53:48.530 --> 00:53:52.686
and so you've probably
got a good exposure--

00:53:52.686 --> 00:53:53.519
- Yeah, and re-engineering required, yeah.

00:53:54.480 --> 00:53:58.330
- That's right, the huge
amount of fat in our system

00:53:58.330 --> 00:54:01.550
that can be cut out with efficiency gains.

00:54:01.550 --> 00:54:06.550
And the policy measures
include regulations

00:54:07.660 --> 00:54:09.850
to impose higher and higher

00:54:09.850 --> 00:54:13.030
fuel efficiency standards on automobiles.

00:54:13.030 --> 00:54:16.570
We can easily get to 60
or 70 mile per gallon

00:54:16.570 --> 00:54:19.500
by the year 2025 if we tell the automakers

00:54:19.500 --> 00:54:20.470
they have to do it.

00:54:20.470 --> 00:54:22.240
If we don't tell them
to do it, they won't,

00:54:22.240 --> 00:54:25.220
but if we do, they must.

00:54:25.220 --> 00:54:29.070
And so fuel efficiency
standards for automobiles

00:54:29.070 --> 00:54:31.860
and for homes, new homes,

00:54:31.860 --> 00:54:34.030
appliance standards for air conditioners,

00:54:34.030 --> 00:54:36.363
refrigerators, and stoves and so forth.

00:54:37.360 --> 00:54:41.080
Then I want to, this is one
of the more radical pieces

00:54:41.080 --> 00:54:44.240
of the plan, one way to think about

00:54:44.240 --> 00:54:48.320
what we're asking for is
that we treat solar and wind

00:54:48.320 --> 00:54:49.800
the way we now treat oil.

00:54:49.800 --> 00:54:52.830
We hugely subsidize oil.

00:54:52.830 --> 00:54:55.670
In fact, the Iraq war, which
some people would argue

00:54:55.670 --> 00:54:58.900
is an oil subsidy because
it was a major motivation

00:54:58.900 --> 00:55:02.950
for the war, is going to
cost over a trillion dollars.

00:55:02.950 --> 00:55:05.440
imagine what you could do
with a trillion dollars

00:55:05.440 --> 00:55:10.440
spent on solar and wind
turbines to produce electricity.

00:55:11.800 --> 00:55:14.960
We could wean ourselves
off of all of our coal

00:55:14.960 --> 00:55:16.950
and about three-quarters of our oil.

00:55:16.950 --> 00:55:20.680
We still need some for some
liquid fuels for aircraft

00:55:20.680 --> 00:55:25.680
and so on, but the replacing
current automobiles

00:55:26.450 --> 00:55:29.070
with rechargeable hybrids
and getting the electricity

00:55:29.070 --> 00:55:31.780
to charge them from wind and sun.

00:55:31.780 --> 00:55:34.210
How do we get society to go there?

00:55:34.210 --> 00:55:39.210
Well, shifting subsidies
and then I want to take

00:55:39.610 --> 00:55:44.610
that foolish tax cut that
Bush gave the wealthy

00:55:45.150 --> 00:55:47.950
and I want to keep that as a tax cut,

00:55:47.950 --> 00:55:49.310
but not for the wealthy.

00:55:49.310 --> 00:55:53.490
I want to make it a tax cut,
a tax break on the profits

00:55:53.490 --> 00:55:56.100
from the sale of clean energy.

00:55:56.100 --> 00:55:59.960
There's a motivation for people
to invest in clean energy.

00:55:59.960 --> 00:56:01.810
It doesn't pick winners in advance

00:56:01.810 --> 00:56:04.250
because if you're not selling clean energy

00:56:04.250 --> 00:56:06.190
'cause you didn't invent the right device

00:56:06.190 --> 00:56:07.910
you don't get the tax cut,

00:56:07.910 --> 00:56:11.920
so it's a tax cut that
automatically targets the winners

00:56:11.920 --> 00:56:16.920
and from what I can
understand of investment

00:56:17.270 --> 00:56:20.140
and technology and economics,

00:56:20.140 --> 00:56:23.320
such a tax shift would cause a flood

00:56:23.320 --> 00:56:26.920
of investment money into
the clean energy sector

00:56:26.920 --> 00:56:30.520
and the combination of shifting subsidies,

00:56:30.520 --> 00:56:34.600
shifting that tax break, and regulations,

00:56:34.600 --> 00:56:36.610
we wouldn't even need a carbon tax,

00:56:36.610 --> 00:56:39.550
which I think is politically
a very tall order.

00:56:39.550 --> 00:56:40.610
I don't think it's gonna be easy

00:56:40.610 --> 00:56:43.630
to get a carbon tax in place,

00:56:43.630 --> 00:56:45.730
so we don't need it if
we do all these things.

